main event: Witness reported an unidentified object in Austin, Pennsylvania on 3 March 1969.
interesting points: Witness saw an object that resembled a kite during the observation., The object made a noise described as 'like tin wobbling.', The sighting lasted approximately five to ten seconds., The object appeared to be moving sideways despite wind direction., The witness chose not to report the observation officially due to fear of being deemed crazy.
sighted object: unidentified flying object resembling a kite
witness description: Lt Marine, who did not officially report the sighting
